{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1008c18a-4cd5-42d2-88ff-24e9d55ba5b4","content":"This is a known breaking change in .NET 10. MAUI now enables **edge-to-edge rendering** by default on Android, which makes `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` ineffective.\n\nYou have two options:\n\n### Option 1 — Opt out of edge-to-edge (quickest fix)\n\nIn `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n    WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, true);\n}\n```\n\nThis restores the .NET 9 behavior — the system resizes your layout when the keyboard opens, and your bottom input bar moves up automatically.\n\n### Option 2 — Keep edge-to-edge + handle insets (recommended)\n\nIf you want the modern edge-to-edge look, react to keyboard insets in `MainActivity.cs`:\n\n```csharp\nusing AndroidX.Core.View;\n\nprotected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)\n{\n    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);\n\n    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new InsetsListener());\n}\n\nprivate class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener\n{\n    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)\n    {\n        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());\n        var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());\n\n        // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset\n        int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);\n        v.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);\n\n        return insets;\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis dynamically pads the bottom of your window by the keyboard height, pushing your input bar up while keeping the edge-to-edge aesthetic.\n\n**Option 1** is the fastest path; **Option 2** is the forward-looking approach.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6a5a1920-1785-4196-810c-0c27a50b1c94","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a .NET MAUI issue with keyboard handling in .NET 10. This is a known change — `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated/removed in Android 11+ and .NET MAUI has been evolving its approach. Let me provide guidance based on what I know.\n\nIn .NET MAUI / Android, `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated at the Android platform level (Android 11/API 30+). In .NET 9, it still partially worked, but in .NET 10, MAUI adopted edge-to-edge rendering by default on Android, which means the old `SoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` approach no longer works.\n\n\nThe modern approach involves working with the new edge-to-edge APIs and `WindowInsets` to detect keyboard visibility and adjust the layout accordingly. The key fix for .NET 10 is handling the edge-to-edge mode that's now enabled by default, which requires adjusting how we manage soft input and keyboard insets. Setting up the MainActivity to opt out of edge-to-edge behavior...","outputTokens":1336,"requestId":"9BC6:35BDDE:6086D54:6BD4923:69EC1147"},"id":"75c6fcfe-cb9d-4241-be7c-19b5d31cd698","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:57:03.936Z","parentId":"33e717e7-35e2-4ca2-86e5-8b2bcffc4d8d"}
